==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Castile soap
<hw>Cas"tile soap`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[From <etsep>Castile</etsep>,
or <etsep>Castilia</etsep>, a province in Spain, from which it
originally came.]</ety> <def>A kind of fine, hard, white or mottled
soap, made with olive oil and soda; also, a soap made in imitation of
the above-described soap.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Castilian</ent>⟦br⟧
